descript.purpose: To display the Solano County, California boundary as a polygon shapefile.
descript.supplinf: Use this as the "official" county boundary shapefile per BSM, June 2006.

citeinfo.origin: This boundary layer aligns with the existing, incomplete Solano Co. Parcel layer version 29.
citeinfo.title: Solano County Boundary Polygon

idinfo.useconst: None. This layer does not represent legal boundaries or legal descriptions of any feature within Solano County, CA. This dataset is not suitable for high-precision measurement applications such as engineering problems, property transfers, or other uses that might require highly accurate measurements of the earth's surface.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Federal information processing standards codes (FIPS codes) are a standardized set of numeric or alphabetic codes issued by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) to ensure uniform identification of geographic entities through all federal government agencies.
